initial_story:
Police have deployed an armoured vehicle to pry open the cabin of a lorry on a motorway in Texas.

The driver refused to stop, or get out of the cab when officers used spike strips to stop the vehicle, police said.

After the armoured vehicle tore open a window, police threw in a gas canister, before going inside and pulling the driver out.

It is unclear what started the chase, but police said the driver used "evasive manoeuvres", changing lanes multiple times and swerving.

“We still don’t know why he was acting in the erratic manner that he was,” Harris County Sheriff Ed Gonzalez told journalists, adding that he appeared to have "some heavy impairment".

Firefighters scrambled to free a driver trapped in a burned-out bus on a rural road in Oregon, as authorities investigated a catastrophic crash caused by reckless racing.

The vehicles, allegedly driven by thrill-seekers on a high-speed joyride, had crossed onto the wrong side of the road multiple times before colliding in the wee hours of the morning.

"We are still trying to piece together what led to this chain reaction," said Oregon State Police Chief, James Brown. "Eyewitnesses reported a black SUV and sports car speeding down the highway before everything spiralled out of control."

Rescuers extricated the lone driver from the bus's mangled debris, and authorities are probing whether intoxication or other substances played a factor in the crash.
